# PowerEdge R730xd profile.
#
# Chassis notes:
# - Six 60mm hot-swap fans
# - BMC clamps PWM <10% to safety RPM (5040), so 0% is impossible —
#   no fan-stall risk. Real BMC floor is 10% PWM = 3840 RPM (probed).
# - Tesla P4 is passive (relies entirely on chassis airflow)
# - RTX A5500 has its own fan but dumps heat into chassis volume
# - CPUs are Xeon E5-2600 v3/v4, TJunction ~85-95°C

: "${MIN_FAN:=10}"             # BMC's hard floor — going lower = same RPM

# IPMI temperature sensors on R730xd's iDRAC8. Probed by querying
# ipmi_temperature_celsius labels at runtime. The two CPU sensors
# share the name "Temp" and are distinguished by FreeIPMI record id
# 26/27 (NOT the BMC raw id from `ipmitool sdr`). Inlet/Exhaust names
# are unique so id isn't needed.
: "${SENSOR_CPU1_NAME:=Temp}"
: "${SENSOR_CPU1_ID:=26}"
: "${SENSOR_CPU2_NAME:=Temp}"
: "${SENSOR_CPU2_ID:=27}"
: "${SENSOR_INLET_NAME:=Inlet Temp}"
: "${SENSOR_EXHAUST_NAME:=Exhaust Temp}"
